President Donald Trump and Nigerian President Muhammadu Buhari shake hands during for a news conference in the Rose Garden of the White House in Washington, Monday, April 30, 2018. (AP Photo/Susan Walsh) Former US President Donald Trump has praised Nigeria’s government for banning Twitter after it deleted President Muhammadu Buhari’s post for allegedly breaching its rules. In a statement, former President DONALD Trump said Twitter cannot dictate good and evil. He urged other countries to ban Twitter and Facebook for not allowing “free and open speech”. Mr Trump was banned from both platforms after the US7 Capitol riot in January.